high-volume or critical production service environment. Experience creating tools for infrastructure (IaaS and PaaS) management and automation. Experienced with DevOps engineering practices, comfortable with diverse technical problem sets across the tech stack. Possess a deep understanding of the Linux operating system and are at home on the terminal. Comfortable operating in environments subject to regulatory, compliance, and risk-based security requirements. Experience in CI/CD toolsets (e.g. Jenkins, GitLab, Sonarqube, etc). Patience and tolerance for when things just go wrong. Excellent communications skills (written, verbal, & virtual). Strong drive, self-motivated, logical, and detail-oriented. Passion for new technologies, software & processes. Ability to multi-task in a fast-paced environment with multiple deadlines is essential. Why You\u2019ll Love Working Here! Highly competitive compensation and benefits package including: Fully-vested 401k matching (up to 10%), 100% company-paid comprehensive healthcare, Unlimited sick leave, All federal holidays & 15 days personal leave, Regular virtual and in-person social events, Flexible schedules, educational reimbursements, and much more. Office hours are flexible with most work performed remotely (as we are a geographically dispersed team), but some actions may require travel and regular team interaction. Most of our team works out of on-trend, workshare office spaces around the nation. Eventually, this position may require a government security clearance. Skyward Federal is a small (but growing) startup bringing the best of breed to the most exciting & unique missions possible. We work hard but play harder. There is constant room for growth and cross-training depending on what your life goals are. Apply now & start your journey today! Note: During the coronavirus pandemic, all employees are working from home with only essential travel to client sites (for classified work) authorized. Job Type: Full-time Pay: $80,000.00 - $140,000.00 per hour Work authorization: United States (Required) Security Clearance Required: Top Secret (Preferred) Work Location: Fully Remote Benefits: Health insurance Dental insurance Vision insurance Retirement plan Signing bonus Paid time off Work from home Flexible schedule Parental leave Relocation assistance Professional development assistance Tuition reimbursement This Company Describes Its Culture as: Detail-oriented -- quality and precision-focused Innovative -- innovative and risk-taking Team-oriented -- cooperative and collaborative This Job Is: A job for which military experienced candidates are encouraged to apply Schedule: Monday to Friday Company's website: skywardfederal.com Work Remotely: Yes "
